Irene Epple of West Germany, an outstanding skier on the women's World Cup circuit since 1973, has decided to relinquish her career to pursue the study of medicine she began in the off-season last year. ''My recent results haven't been that good and I thought I should make way for some younger girls,'' said Miss Epple, who is 27 and who was second to

Erika Hess of Switzerland in the final World Cup standing in 1982. . . .

Bill Johnson of the United States was ill yesterday with an intestinal flu and doubtful for the competition before Sunday.